$ whichpm

→ https://github.com/mklement0/whichpm/blob/master/bin/whichpm[whichpm] is a cross-platform script that, analogous to → Linux/shell/commands/which[the `which` command line utility],
locates installed → development/languages/Perl/modules[Perl modules] by their package name.

Show location (installation directory):
code {
$ whichpm Time::HiRes
/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/perl/5.22/Time/HiRes.pm
code }

Show a module's version
code {
$ whichpm -v → development/languages/Perl/modules/Geo/Coordinates/Converter/LV03[Geo::Coordinates::Converter::LV03]
Geo::Coordinates::Converter::LV03	0.02	(non-core)	/usr/local/share/perl/5.22.1/Geo/Coordinates/Converter/LV03.pm
code }

Show the paths of all installed modules:
code {
$ whichpm -a
code }

sa:
  → development/languages/Perl/modules/_scripts_/find-installed-perl-modules[`find-installed-perl-modules.pl`] is a quick and dirty script to find the locations (paths) of installed
  Perl modules on a computer.

  → http://www.perlmonks.org/?node=whichpm

  → development/languages/Perl/perldoc#perldoc-l[`perldoc -l Module::Name`]
